<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Why don't I see my representatives?</h3>
<p>
Make sure your home address is entered correctly. Tap <strong>Edit Address</strong> on the dashboard and re-enter your full street address, city, state, and ZIP code.
</p>

<h3>Why are there no state bills in my feed?</h3>
<p>
State bills are loaded based on your address. If your address is new or was recently updated, pull down to refresh the dashboard. If the problem persists, contact us.
</p>

<h3>Why does the Vote Record show no votes for a representative?</h3>
<p>
Vote history is not available for all representatives. Federal votes are broadly supported. State vote data depends on your state's reporting and may not be available for every legislator.
</p>

<h3>How do I change my interests?</h3>
<p>
Tap the menu icon in the top-left corner of the dashboard and select <strong>Interests</strong>. Your feed will update automatically on your next visit to the dashboard.
</p>

<h3>How do I contact my representative?</h3>
<p>
Tap any bill in your feed to open the bill detail screen, then tap the <strong>Contact Your Rep</strong> button. You can also go to <strong>My Reps</strong> from the side menu to contact representatives directly.
</p>

